    <div class="row ceg-t35">
        <div class="large-9 small-10 large-centered small-centered column">
            <ul class="bullet-list">
            	<li><strong>Clip-Down Nursing Tanks:</strong> While breastfeeding, you will want to stock up on nursing camisoles that have a clip-down function for effortless access. Available in fitted and flowy designs, you have a choice based on your sense of style and comfort level. Get a bundle of colors from basic to bold, like black, white and gray to red, yellow and pink. For a stylish post-pregnancy look, pair your nursing tank top with a draped cardigan and jogger pants—or swap the joggers for <a href="{{ENV_HOSTNAME}}/shop/womens-clothing/maternity-clothes/Department_type/Leggings?id=66718">maternity leggings</a>.</li>
				<li><strong>Wrap Nursing Tops:</strong> Wrap nursing tops provide a more pulled-together look for your day-to-play style. During mealtimes or pumping sessions, simply untie or pull down the neckline of your top for access. Some faux-wrap nursing tops can also double as nursing wraps. Do you want your nursing look to stand out? Get a wrap nursing top in a vivid floral print or stripes. Want a more versatile look? Neutral colors, like black, gray and navy blue, will coordinate with all your favorite outfits. Partner your wrap nursing top with skinny pants for a chic, casual look—or dress it down with jeans.</li>
				<li><strong>Tiered Nursing Tops:</strong> What is a tiered nursing top? A tiered nursing top has various layers. Simply, lift the top layer during feedings and to pump. Make a stylish statement in prints or keep it classic in solids. Pair your tiered nursing top with your go-to jeans for a casual-chic look.</li>
            </ul>
