	            <li><strong>Yoga Pants:</strong> After you give birth you will want to wear comfortable pants with an elastic waistband, so yoga pants and sweats are your best bets while you’re still recuperating. Looking for a more trend-right option? Jogger pants are also super-comfy. Take your look up a notch with printed joggers, like leopard, camo and floral. Link up your yoga pants or joggers with your favorite T-shirts.</li>
				<li><strong>Post-Pregnancy Leggings:</strong> After you have finished recuperating from giving birth, post-pregnancy leggings will be ideal to wear until you’re able get back to your pre-pregnancy self. They feature a high-waist design for sleek shaping. Pair your nursing tops with post-pregnancy leggings for a polished, casual look.</li>
				<li><strong>Pull-On Skirts:</strong> When it’s too hot for pants, pull-on skirts are a great option for a comfortable fit. From above-the-knee to maxi styles, pull-on skirts will lend a feminine feel to your nursing tops.</li>
